{"path":"\t<a class='XURL content-link' href='\/' data-target='root' data-title=''>&#8962; <\/a>\n\t<span class='path-separator'>\\<\/span>\n","async":"0","date":"2018 Oct 07","desc":"Pitch describing","content":"<div id='message'> <p> I have always wondered - why do we all still have to go through the same troubles when exchanging numbers especially over phone by speech. Isn't there a better way? <\/p> <ul> <li>How often mistakes are made when sending IDs like mobile numbers and email addresses<\/li> <li>In absence of a pen, having to remember even a 10 digit number can become a difficult task<\/li> <li>If there is no internet or pen-drive - how to send a small digital file?<\/li> <li>What if correct delivery is a matter of life and death?<\/li> <\/ul> <p> <a class=\"content-link XURL\" href=\"\/\" data-target=\"root\" data-title=''>WCode<\/a> is the answer. <\/p> <div class=\"center\"> <div> <img src=\"\/resource\/comics_1.png\" alt=\"WCode number example - comics\"\/> <img src=\"\/resource\/comics_2.png\" alt=\"WCode number example - comics\"\/> <\/div> <div> <img src=\"\/resource\/comics_3.png\" alt=\"WCode number example - comics\"\/> <img src=\"\/resource\/comics_4.png\" alt=\"WCode number example - comics\"\/> <\/div> <\/div> <h2>What is WCode?<\/h2> <p> An encoding schema to convert digital data into literal words. It is similar to bar-codes and QR-codes but different in that it is human readable. <\/p> <div id=\"codes-example\"> <table id=\"codes-table\"> <tbody> <tr class=\"code_label\"> <td> Bar Code <\/td> <td> QR Code <\/td> <td> WCode <\/td> <\/tr> <tr class=\"code\"> <td> <span id='bar-code' class='image' title='Bar Code : Rectangle with black bars'><svg xmlns='http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg' x='0px' y='0px' viewBox=\"0 0 126.3 78.9\"> <g fill='#A9A9A9'> <polygon points=\"2,78.9 0,78.9 0,39.5 0,0 2,0 3.9,0 3.9,39.5 3.9,78.9\"\/> <polygon points=\"6.3,78.9 5.5,78.9 5.5,39.5 5.5,0 6.3,0 7.1,0 7.1,39.5 7.1,78.9\"\/> <polygon points=\"13.8,78.9 11,78.9 11